                <div type="section" xml:id="EFT-KB-MARKS-SIGNS-article-5">
                    <head type="section" tid="29">Note for # 77 of minor marks in PP 10k: </head>

                    <p tid="30">In the context of the 80 minor marks, the palms and soles are said in many such lists to be marked with auspicious symbols such
                        as the svastika and śrīvatsa. This is presumably in addition to the thousand-spoked wheels mentioned above and in most lists of the 32
                        major marks. The mention of the palm and sole markings in lists of the 32 major marks in the Lalitavistara and Rāṣṭrapālaparipṛcchā both
                        mention svastikas in addition to wheels. In the list of the 80 minor marks in the Lalitavistara (7.103), however, the equivalent to this
                        mention of markings on the palms and soles refers instead to Prince Siddhartha’s hair as curling into shapes such as the svastika and
                        śrīvatsa.</p>
